{
 "title": "Refutation of Graffiti Conjecture 143 (Gate-4 clean-room rebuild)",
 "slug": "graffiti-143",
 "conjecture_verbatim": "143. variance of positive eigenvalues \u2264 size / average distance.  [S. Fajtlowicz, \"Written on the Wall\" (Graffiti), July 2004 compilation, p.65; \u2264 glyph = cmsy 0x14]",
 "operational_statement": "For every connected graph G: population variance of the strictly positive adjacency eigenvalues <= m / l(G), where m = |E(G)| and l(G) = average distance. Reading N2: l = 2W/n^2 (all ordered pairs incl. diagonal; Roucairol-Cazenave ECAI 2025 code). Reading PAIRS: l = 2W/(n(n-1)) (distinct pairs; Aouchiche-Hansen).",
